[30;1m364 | [0m[35mFTPS (FTP over TLS/SSL) server[0m
[30;1m365 | [0m[35m==============================[0m
[30;1m366 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m367 | [0m[35mpyftpdlib implements FTP over TLS, also known as FTPS, as defined in[0m
[30;1m368 | [0m[35m`RFC-4217`_. This requires installing `PyOpenSSL`_ third party module.[0m
[30;1m369 | [0m[35m`TLS_FTPHandler`_ class requires a ``certfile`` and a ``keyfile``. You can[0m
[30;1m370 | [0m[35mgenerate self-signed SSL certificates like this (see also `Apache FAQs`_):[0m

[31m--[ [0m[34mMatch #[0m[33m369[0m[34m of [0m[33m1072[0m[31m ]--[0m
   Rule Id: [34mBD000600[0m
       Tag: [34mSecurity.Backdoor.LOLBAS.Windows[0m
  Severity: [36mModerate[0m, Confidence: [36mLow[0m
  Filename: [33m/pyftpdlib-2.0.1/docs/tutorial.rst[0m
   Pattern: [32m\s(advpack\.dll|appvlp|at|atbroker|bash|bginfo|bitsadmin|cdb|certutil|cl_invocation\.ps1|cl_mutexverifiers\.ps1|cmd|cmdkey|cmstp|comsvcs\.dll|control|csc|cscript|csi|devtoolslauncher|dfsvc|diskshadow|dnscmd|dnx|dotnet|dxcap|esentutl|eventvwr|excel|expand|extexport|extrac32|findstr|forfiles|ftp|gfxdownloadwrapper|gpscript|hh|ie4uinit|ieadvpack\.dll|ieaframe\.dll|ic|infdefaultinstall|installutil|jsc|makecab|manage-bde\.wsf|mavinject|mftrace|microsoft\.workflow\.compiler|mmc|msbuild|msconfig|msdeploy|msdt|mshta|mshtml\.dll|msc|msxsl|netsh|odbcconf|pcalua|pcwrun|pcwutl\.dll|pester\.bat|powerpnt|presentationhost|pubprn\.vbs|rcsi|reg|regasm|regedit|register-cimprovider|regsvcs|regsvr32|rpcping|rundll32|runonce|runscripthelper|sc|schtasks|scriptrunner|setupapi\.dll|shdocvw\.dll|shell32\.dll|slmgr\.vbs|sqldumper|sqlps|sqltoolsps|squirrel|syncappvpublishingserver|syncappvpublishingserver\.vbs|syssetup\.dll|te|tracker|tttracer|update|url\.dll|verclsid|vsjitdebugger|wab|winrm\.vbs|winword|wmic|wscript|wsl|wsreset|xwizard|zipfldr\.dll)\s[0m
[30;1m316 | [0m[35m        main()[0m
[30;1m317 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m318 | [0m[35mIt must be noted that the multi-thread approach should NOT be used with[0m
[30;1m319 | [0m[35m`UnixAuthorizer`_ or `WindowsAuthorizer`_ . Reason: every time the FTP server[0m
[30;1m320 | [0m[35maccesses the filesystem (e.g. for creating or renaming a file) the authorizer[0m
[30;1m321 | [0m[35mwill temporarily impersonate the currently logged on user by changing effective[0m
[30;1m322 | [0m[35muser or group ID of the current process.[0m

[31m--[ [0m[34mMatch #[0m[33m370[0m[34m of [0m[33m1072[0m[31m ]--[0m
   Rule Id: [34mBD000600[0m
       Tag: [34mSecurity.Backdoor.LOLBAS.Windows[0m
  Severity: [36mModerate[0m, Confidence: [36mLow[0m
  Filename: [33m/pyftpdlib-2.0.1/docs/tutorial.rst[0m
   Pattern: [32m\s(advpack\.dll|appvlp|at|atbroker|bash|bginfo|bitsadmin|cdb|certutil|cl_invocation\.ps1|cl_mutexverifiers\.ps1|cmd|cmdkey|cmstp|comsvcs\.dll|control|csc|cscript|csi|devtoolslauncher|dfsvc|diskshadow|dnscmd|dnx|dotnet|dxcap|esentutl|eventvwr|excel|expand|extexport|extrac32|findstr|forfiles|ftp|gfxdownloadwrapper|gpscript|hh|ie4uinit|ieadvpack\.dll|ieaframe\.dll|ic|infdefaultinstall|installutil|jsc|makecab|manage-bde\.wsf|mavinject|mftrace|microsoft\.workflow\.compiler|mmc|msbuild|msconfig|msdeploy|msdt|mshta|mshtml\.dll|msc|msxsl|netsh|odbcconf|pcalua|pcwrun|pcwutl\.dll|pester\.bat|powerpnt|presentationhost|pubprn\.vbs|rcsi|reg|regasm|regedit|register-cimprovider|regsvcs|regsvr32|rpcping|rundll32|runonce|runscripthelper|sc|schtasks|scriptrunner|setupapi\.dll|shdocvw\.dll|shell32\.dll|slmgr\.vbs|sqldumper|sqlps|sqltoolsps|squirrel|syncappvpublishingserver|syncappvpublishingserver\.vbs|syssetup\.dll|te|tracker|tttracer|update|url\.dll|verclsid|vsjitdebugger|wab|winrm\.vbs|winword|wmic|wscript|wsl|wsreset|xwizard|zipfldr\.dll)\s[0m
[30;1m265 | [0m[35mmodel has one big drawback though: the code cannot contain instructions that[0m
[30;1m266 | [0m[35mblock for a long period of time, otherwise the whole FTP server will hang. As[0m
[30;1m267 | [0m[35msuch, the user should avoid calls such as ``time.sleep(3)``, heavy DB queries,[0m
[30;1m268 | [0m[35metc. at all costs.  There are cases where the async model is not appropriate,[0m
[30;1m269 | [0m[35me.g. if you're dealing with a particularly slow disk or a network filesystem.[0m
[30;1m270 | [0m[35mIf the calls that interact with the filesystem are slow (e.g., ``open(file,[0m
[30;1m271 | [0m[35m'r').read(8192)`` takes 2 seconds to complete) then you are stuck. In such[0m

[30;1m263 | [0m[35mprocess/thread to handle multiple client connections and file transfers. This[0m
[30;1m264 | [0m[35mis why it is so fast, lightweight and scalable (see `benchmarks`_). The async[0m
[30;1m265 | [0m[35mmodel has one big drawback though: the code cannot contain instructions that[0m
[30;1m266 | [0m[35mblock for a long period of time, otherwise the whole FTP server will hang. As[0m
[30;1m267 | [0m[35msuch, the user should avoid calls such as ``time.sleep(3)``, heavy DB queries,[0m
[30;1m268 | [0m[35metc. at all costs.  There are cases where the async model is not appropriate,[0m
[30;1m269 | [0m[35me.g. if you're dealing with a particularly slow disk or a network filesystem.[0m

[30;1m364 | [0m[35mFTPS (FTP over TLS/SSL) server[0m
[30;1m365 | [0m[35m==============================[0m
[30;1m366 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m367 | [0m[35mpyftpdlib implements FTP over TLS, also known as FTPS, as defined in[0m
[30;1m368 | [0m[35m`RFC-4217`_. This requires installing `PyOpenSSL`_ third party module.[0m
[30;1m369 | [0m[35m`TLS_FTPHandler`_ class requires a ``certfile`` and a ``keyfile``. You can[0m
[30;1m370 | [0m[35mgenerate self-signed SSL certificates like this (see also `Apache FAQs`_):[0m

[31m--[ [0m[34mMatch #[0m[33m390[0m[34m of [0m[33m1072[0m[31m ]--[0m
   Rule Id: [34mBD000610[0m
       Tag: [34mSecurity.Backdoor.LOLBAS.Linux[0m
  Severity: [36mModerate[0m, Confidence: [36mLow[0m
  Filename: [33m/pyftpdlib-2.0.1/docs/tutorial.rst[0m
   Pattern: [32m\s(apt|apt\-get|aria2c|arp|ash|awk|base64|bash|bpftrace|busybox|cat|chmod|chown|cp|cpan|cpulimit|crontab|csh|curl|cut|dash|dd|diff|dmesg|dmsetup|dnf|docker|dpkg|easy_install|ed|emacs|env|expand|expect|facter|find|finger|flock|fmt|ftp|gawk|gdb|gimp|git|grep|head|iftop|ionice|ip|irb|jjs|journalctl|jrunscript|ksh|ld\.so|ldconfig|logsave|ltrace|lua|mail|mawk|mount|mtr|mv|mysql|nano|nawk|nc|nice|nl|nmap|node|od|openssl|perl|pg|php|pic|pico|pip|puppet|readelf|red|rlogin|rlwrap|rpm|rpmquery|rsync|ruby|run\-mailcap|run\-parts|rvim|scp|screen|script|sed|service|setarch|sftp|shuf|smbclient|socat|sort|sqlite3|ssh|start\-stop\-daemon|stdbuf|strace|systemctl|tail|tar|taskset|tclsh|tcpdump|tee|telnet|tftp|time|timeout|tmux|top|ul|unexpand|uniq|unshare|vi|vim|watch|wget|whois|wish|xargs|xxd|yum|zsh|zypper)\s[0m
[30;1m332 | [0m[35mmodel, handling multiple concurrent connections, but the workload is split.[0m
[30;1m333 | [0m[35mThis way the delay introduced by a blocking function call is amortized and[0m
[30;1m334 | [0m[35mdivided by the number of workers, and thus also the disk I/O latency is[0m
[30;1m335 | [0m[35mminimized. Every time a new connection comes in, the parent process will[0m
[30;1m336 | [0m[35mautomatically delegate the connection to one of the worker processes, so from[0m
[30;1m337 | [0m[35mthe app standpoint this is completely transparent. As a general rule, it is[0m
[30;1m338 | [0m[35malways a good idea to use this model in production. The optimal value depends[0m

[31m--[ [0m[34mMatch #[0m[33m391[0m[34m of [0m[33m1072[0m[31m ]--[0m
   Rule Id: [34mBD000610[0m
       Tag: [34mSecurity.Backdoor.LOLBAS.Linux[0m
  Severity: [36mModerate[0m, Confidence: [36mLow[0m
  Filename: [33m/pyftpdlib-2.0.1/docs/tutorial.rst[0m

[30;1m270 | [0m[35mIf the calls that interact with the filesystem are slow (e.g., ``open(file,[0m
[30;1m271 | [0m[35m'r').read(8192)`` takes 2 seconds to complete) then you are stuck. In such[0m
[30;1m272 | [0m[35mcases you can change the concurrency model from async to multi processes or[0m
[30;1m273 | [0m[35mmulti threads. In practice this means that every time a client connects, a[0m
[30;1m274 | [0m[35mseparate thread or process is spawned, and internally it will run its own IO[0m
[30;1m275 | [0m[35mloop.[0m
[30;1m276 | [0m[35m[0m

[30;1m263 | [0m[35mprocess/thread to handle multiple client connections and file transfers. This[0m

[30;1m266 | [0m[35mblock for a long period of time, otherwise the whole FTP server will hang. As[0m

[30;1m268 | [0m[35metc. at all costs.  There are cases where the async model is not appropriate,[0m
[30;1m269 | [0m[35me.g. if you're dealing with a particularly slow disk or a network filesystem.[0m

[30;1m88 | [0m[35m============[0m
[30;1m89 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m90 | [0m[35mDespite being written in an interpreted language, pyftpdlib has transfer rates[0m
[30;1m91 | [0m[35mcomparable or superior to common UNIX FTP servers written in C. It usually[0m
[30;1m92 | [0m[35mtends to scale better (see `benchmarks`_) because whereas vsftpd and proftpd[0m
[30;1m93 | [0m[35muse multiple processes to achieve concurrency, pyftpdlib only uses one (see[0m
[30;1m94 | [0m[35m`the C10K problem`_).[0m

[31m--[ [0m[34mMatch #[0m[33m465[0m[34m of [0m[33m1072[0m[31m ]--[0m
   Rule Id: [34mBD000600[0m
       Tag: [34mSecurity.Backdoor.LOLBAS.Windows[0m

[31m--[ [0m[34mMatch #[0m[33m474[0m[34m of [0m[33m1072[0m[31m ]--[0m
   Rule Id: [34mBD000610[0m
       Tag: [34mSecurity.Backdoor.LOLBAS.Linux[0m
  Severity: [36mModerate[0m, Confidence: [36mLow[0m
  Filename: [33m/pyftpdlib-2.0.1/README.rst[0m
   Pattern: [32m\s(apt|apt\-get|aria2c|arp|ash|awk|base64|bash|bpftrace|busybox|cat|chmod|chown|cp|cpan|cpulimit|crontab|csh|curl|cut|dash|dd|diff|dmesg|dmsetup|dnf|docker|dpkg|easy_install|ed|emacs|env|expand|expect|facter|find|finger|flock|fmt|ftp|gawk|gdb|gimp|git|grep|head|iftop|ionice|ip|irb|jjs|journalctl|jrunscript|ksh|ld\.so|ldconfig|logsave|ltrace|lua|mail|mawk|mount|mtr|mv|mysql|nano|nawk|nc|nice|nl|nmap|node|od|openssl|perl|pg|php|pic|pico|pip|puppet|readelf|red|rlogin|rlwrap|rpm|rpmquery|rsync|ruby|run\-mailcap|run\-parts|rvim|scp|screen|script|sed|service|setarch|sftp|shuf|smbclient|socat|sort|sqlite3|ssh|start\-stop\-daemon|stdbuf|strace|systemctl|tail|tar|taskset|tclsh|tcpdump|tee|telnet|tftp|time|timeout|tmux|top|ul|unexpand|uniq|unshare|vi|vim|watch|wget|whois|wish|xargs|xxd|yum|zsh|zypper)\s[0m
[30;1m88 | [0m[35m============[0m
[30;1m89 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m90 | [0m[35mDespite being written in an interpreted language, pyftpdlib has transfer rates[0m
[30;1m91 | [0m[35mcomparable or superior to common UNIX FTP servers written in C. It usually[0m
[30;1m92 | [0m[35mtends to scale better (see `benchmarks`_) because whereas vsftpd and proftpd[0m
[30;1m93 | [0m[35muse multiple processes to achieve concurrency, pyftpdlib only uses one (see[0m
[30;1m94 | [0m[35m`the C10K problem`_).[0m

[31m--[ [0m[34mMatch #[0m[33m475[0m[34m of [0m[33m1072[0m[31m ]--[0m
   Rule Id: [34mBD000610[0m
       Tag: [34mSecurity.Backdoor.LOLBAS.Linux[0m

[30;1m8 | [0m[35m============[0m
[30;1m9 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m10 | [0m[35mThis page lists the standard Internet RFCs that define the FTP protocol.[0m

[30;1m12 | [0m[35m`RFC-1123`_, implementing all the fundamental commands and features described[0m
[30;1m13 | [0m[35min them. It also implements some more (relatively) recent features such as OPTS[0m
[30;1m14 | [0m[35mand FEAT commands (`RFC-2398`_), EPRT and EPSV commands to implement IPv6[0m

[30;1m8 | [0m[35m============[0m
[30;1m9 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m10 | [0m[35mThis page lists the standard Internet RFCs that define the FTP protocol.[0m
[30;1m11 | [0m[35mpyftpdlib conforms to the FTP protocol standard as defined in `RFC-959`_ and[0m
[30;1m12 | [0m[35m`RFC-1123`_, implementing all the fundamental commands and features described[0m
[30;1m13 | [0m[35min them. It also implements some more (relatively) recent features such as OPTS[0m
[30;1m14 | [0m[35mand FEAT commands (`RFC-2398`_), EPRT and EPSV commands to implement IPv6[0m

[30;1m73 | [0m[35mHow can I run long-running tasks without blocking the server?[0m
[30;1m74 | [0m[35m-------------------------------------------------------------[0m
[30;1m75 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m76 | [0m[35mpyftpdlib is an *asynchronous* FTP server. That means that if you need to run a[0m
[30;1m77 | [0m[35mtime consuming task you have to use a separate Python process or thread,[0m
[30;1m78 | [0m[35motherwise the entire asynchronous loop will be blocked.[0m
[30;1m79 | [0m[35m[0m

[30;1m190 | [0m[35mthe FTP server should return a directory listing over the command channel.[0m
[30;1m191 | [0m[35m`RFC-959`_ does not explicitly mention globbing; this means that FTP servers[0m
[30;1m192 | [0m[35mare not required to support globbing in order to be compliant.  However, many[0m
[30;1m193 | [0m[35mFTP servers do support globbing as a measure of convenience for FTP clients and[0m
[30;1m194 | [0m[35musers. In order to search for and match the given globbing expression, the code[0m
[30;1m195 | [0m[35mhas to search (possibly) many directories, examine each contained filename, and[0m
[30;1m196 | [0m[35mbuild a list of matching files in memory. Since this operation can be quite[0m

[30;1m451 | [0m[35m  A class used to interact with the filesystem, providing a cross-platform[0m

[30;1m5 | [0m[35m.. contents:: Table of Contents[0m
[30;1m6 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m7 | [0m[35mpyftpdlib implements the server side of the FTP protocol as defined in[0m
[30;1m8 | [0m[35m`RFC-959 <https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc959.html>`_. This document is intended to[0m
[30;1m9 | [0m[35mserve as a simple API reference of most important classes and functions.[0m
[30;1m10 | [0m[35mAlso see the `tutorial <tutorial.html>`_ document.[0m

[30;1m135 | [0m[35m============[0m
[30;1m136 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m137 | [0m[35mDespite being written in an interpreted language, pyftpdlib has transfer rates[0m
[30;1m138 | [0m[35mcomparable or superior to common UNIX FTP servers written in C. It usually[0m
[30;1m139 | [0m[35mtends to scale better (see `benchmarks`_) because whereas vsftpd and proftpd[0m
[30;1m140 | [0m[35muse multiple processes to achieve concurrency, pyftpdlib only uses one (see[0m
[30;1m141 | [0m[35m`the C10K problem`_).[0m

[30;1m135 | [0m[35m============[0m
[30;1m136 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m137 | [0m[35mDespite being written in an interpreted language, pyftpdlib has transfer rates[0m
[30;1m138 | [0m[35mcomparable or superior to common UNIX FTP servers written in C. It usually[0m
[30;1m139 | [0m[35mtends to scale better (see `benchmarks`_) because whereas vsftpd and proftpd[0m
[30;1m140 | [0m[35muse multiple processes to achieve concurrency, pyftpdlib only uses one (see[0m
[30;1m141 | [0m[35m`the C10K problem`_).[0m

[30;1m135 | [0m[35m============[0m
[30;1m136 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m137 | [0m[35mDespite being written in an interpreted language, pyftpdlib has transfer rates[0m
[30;1m138 | [0m[35mcomparable or superior to common UNIX FTP servers written in C. It usually[0m
[30;1m139 | [0m[35mtends to scale better (see `benchmarks`_) because whereas vsftpd and proftpd[0m
[30;1m140 | [0m[35muse multiple processes to achieve concurrency, pyftpdlib only uses one (see[0m
[30;1m141 | [0m[35m`the C10K problem`_).[0m

[31m--[ [0m[34mMatch #[0m[33m1030[0m[34m of [0m[33m1072[0m[31m ]--[0m
   Rule Id: [34mBD000600[0m
       Tag: [34mSecurity.Backdoor.LOLBAS.Windows[0m

[30;1m135 | [0m[35m============[0m
[30;1m136 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m137 | [0m[35mDespite being written in an interpreted language, pyftpdlib has transfer rates[0m
[30;1m138 | [0m[35mcomparable or superior to common UNIX FTP servers written in C. It usually[0m
[30;1m139 | [0m[35mtends to scale better (see `benchmarks`_) because whereas vsftpd and proftpd[0m
[30;1m140 | [0m[35muse multiple processes to achieve concurrency, pyftpdlib only uses one (see[0m
[30;1m141 | [0m[35m`the C10K problem`_).[0m
